# =============================================================================
# Aetheron-X Environment Variables Configuration
# =============================================================================
# Copy this file to .env.local and update with your actual values
# DO NOT commit .env.local to version control as it contains secrets
# =============================================================================

# Database Configuration
# ----------------------
# DATABASE_URL: SQLite database connection string
# Format: file:<path-to-database-file>
# 
# For development locally, use an absolute path:
# DATABASE_URL=file:C:/Users/YourUsername/path/to/Aetheron-X/prisma/dev.db
#
# For production (e.g., Azure, Vercel), use:
# - Absolute path if deploying with mounted volumes
# - Or use environment variable expansion if supported by your platform
#
# The app will create a SQLite database file if it doesn't exist.
DATABASE_URL=file:./prisma/dev.db

# Authentication Configuration
# ----------------------------
# AETHERX_ADMIN_EMAIL: Email for the default admin user created on first run
# Default: admin@aetherx.local
AETHERX_ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@aetherx.local

# AETHERX_ADMIN_PASSWORD: Password for the default admin user created on first run
# IMPORTANT: Change this in production!
# Default: aetherx-dev-password
AETHERX_ADMIN_PASSWORD=aetherx-dev-password

# AETHERX_SESSION_SECRET: Secret key for signing session tokens
# IMPORTANT: Use a strong, random value in production (e.g., from `openssl rand -base64 32`)
# This is critical for security - if compromised, all user sessions are at risk
# Default: replace-with-a-strong-random-secret
AETHERX_SESSION_SECRET=replace-with-a-strong-random-secret

# =============================================================================
# Setup Instructions
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. Copy this file:
#    cp .env.example .env.local
#
# 2. Update values in .env.local:
#    - Change DATABASE_URL to your database path (use absolute path for Windows)
#    - Change AETHERX_ADMIN_PASSWORD to a secure password
#    - Generate a strong AETHERX_SESSION_SECRET using:
#      - On Linux/Mac: openssl rand -base64 32
#      - On Windows: [Convert]::ToBase64String([System.Security.Cryptography.RNGCryptoServiceProvider]::new().GetBytes(24))
#
# 3. Run the development server:
#    npm run dev
#
# 4. Access the application:
#    http://localhost:3000
#
# 5. Login with admin credentials set above
#
# =============================================================================
# Windows Path Note
# =============================================================================
# On Windows, use forward slashes (/) in file paths, not backslashes (\):
#   CORRECT:   DATABASE_URL=file:C:/Users/Username/projects/prisma/dev.db
#   INCORRECT: DATABASE_URL=file:C:\Users\Username\projects\prisma\dev.db
#
# =============================================================================
# Production Deployment
# =============================================================================
# When deploying to production platforms (Vercel, Azure, etc.):
#
# 1. Set environment variables via your platform's configuration:
#    - Vercel: Project Settings > Environment Variables
#    - Azure: App Service > Settings > Configuration
#    - Docker: docker run -e DATABASE_URL="..." ...
#
# 2. Use a persistent database storage:
#    - For Vercel: Use neon.tech or another managed database
#    - For Azure: Use Azure SQL Database or Cosmos DB
#    - For Docker: Mount volumes for SQLite file persistence
#
# 3. Generate secure secrets:
#    - AETHERX_ADMIN_PASSWORD: Strong password with special characters
#    - AETHERX_SESSION_SECRET: Cryptographically secure random string
#
# 4. Example Vercel deployment:
#    vercel env add DATABASE_URL
#    vercel env add AETHERX_ADMIN_PASSWORD
#    vercel env add AETHERX_SESSION_SECRET
#    vercel deploy --prod
#
# =============================================================================
